   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID-19 Emergency Appeal (HSU-0049)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The COVID19 pandemic and subsequent lockdowns have disproportionately hurt marginalized communities due to loss of livelihood and lack of access&#xA0;to food, shelter, health, and other basic needs. This has choked off almost all-economic activities leading to widespread loss of jobs and incomes for informal workers and the poor that in turn causes untold misery for them.&#xA0; This initiatives seeks to support these vulnerable communities by providing food and nutrition security, water, sanitation and health, essential health supplies for service providers, and unconditional cash transfers, and&#xA0;training of humanitarian staff and government frontline workers along with communications/materials on COVID19 in local language.</narrative>
  </description>
